ated intensity ratios, such as $W_{\\rm CO\\,(3-2)}$/$W_{\\rm\nCO\\,(2-1)}\\gtrsim0.8$ and $W_{\\rm CO\\,(2-1)}$/$W_{\\rm CO\\,(1-0)}\\gtrsim1.2$,\ncan be used as a tracer of gas compressed regions with a relatively high\ntemperature and density. This further suggests that the non-Gaussian part of\nthe line-ratio distribution can be used to trace the interaction between the\nmolecular gas and the hot gas in the bubble.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Aug 2019 14:20:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 16 Oct 2019 09:28:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-06"}
